# Constants Pattern

## What belongs here

Non-secret, non-credential default values that can be overridden via environment variables.
One file per service domain.

| File | Domain |
|---|---|
| `app.py` | Runtime switches (`DATABASE_CONFIGURATION`, `ENVIRONMENT`, `DEV_OUTPUTS`) |
| `llm.py` | Model selection and timeouts |
| `mongo.py` | Collection names, index names, retry/timeout settings |
| `pinecone.py` | Pinecone index name, namespace, host, environment |
| `supabase.py` | Supabase project URL |
| `upstash.py` | Redis URL and rate-limit defaults |
| `vertex.py` | GCP project ID and region |

## What does NOT belong here

- API keys, tokens, passwords, or any secret credential
- URIs that contain embedded credentials
- Hardcoded production values that differ per deployment without an override path

## Every constant must have a Settings field

Every constant exported from this package must be mirrored as a field in `SharedSettings`
or `Settings` in `app/core/config.py`, so it can be overridden via environment variable.

```python
# ✅ constants/mongo.py
MONGODB_DB_NAME = "rav_dev"

# ✅ core/config.py
mongodb_db_name: str = C.MONGODB_DB_NAME
```

## Backend-conditional imports

Constants specific to a vector-store backend are conditionally imported in `__init__.py`.
Keep the conditional block in `__init__.py`, not scattered across files:

```python
if DATABASE_CONFIGURATION == DataBaseConfiguration.PINECONE:
    from rag.app.core.constants.pinecone import (  # noqa: F401
        PINECONE_INDEX_NAME, PINECONE_NAMESPACE, ...
    )
```

## Re-export everything from `__init__.py`

All consumer code imports from `rag.app.core.constants` (the package), never from sub-modules directly.
